Package emissary.core

Class HDMobileAgent

java.lang.Object
emissary.core.MobileAgent
emissary.core.HDMobileAgent
All Implemented Interfaces:
IMobileAgent, MobileAgentMBean, Serializable, Runnable
public class HDMobileAgent extends MobileAgent
This mobile agent carries around an ArrayList of payload that can be added onto instead of sprouting. The agent is responsible for getting all payloads on the list processed to completion before going idle

    • go

      public void go(Object payload, IServiceProviderPlace arrivalPlace)
      Description copied from class: MobileAgent
      A little more than the name implies, this method sets the things required for an idle agent to get moving again. This is to be used when starting the agent from a pick up place because although we start with an initial 'place' we don't use it for processing, just to get the nextKey from the directory there.
      Specified by:

    • agentControl

      protected void agentControl(IServiceProviderPlace currentPlaceArg)
      The main control loop to determine and go through an itinerary Since we have a list of payload object that can potentially grow at every place we visit, we need to iterate over them until we get done but we cannot use a normal iterator which will throw an exception if the underlying collection mutates while iterating. So we make the selection of the first payload that needs work, find the place for it, process all other payloads that have the same form and lastPlace, then move on.
      Overrides:
      agentControl in class MobileAgent
      Parameters:
      currentPlaceArg - where we are now
